ddObj.Name: pck_API_PT_StateEcu01_1024
ddObj.ddProperty: Global (external) struct, which forms the data based API to access the signal values of frame StateEcu01 (1024, 0x400). A (hypothetic) ECU provided message we can read the current speed of rotation of the engine from

ddObj.Name: checksum
ddObj.ddProperty: Instance of signals.checksum. Message related checksum. The sum is defined such that the arithmetic sum of all message bytes (including the check sum itself) and the start value yields 0xff

ddObj.Name: speedOfRotation
ddObj.ddProperty: Instance of signals.speedOfRotation. Speed of rotation of the engine

ddObj.Name: LocalScaling
ddObj.ddProperty: Local linear scaling for signal speedOfRotation

ddObj.Name: sequenceCounter
ddObj.ddProperty: Instance of signals.sequenceCounter. Sequence counter of message origin. Each update of the message contents results in a cylically increased counter value. The counter wraps around after 14

ddObj.Name: pck_API_PT_StateEcu02_1040
ddObj.ddProperty: Global (external) struct, which forms the data based API to access the signal values of frame StateEcu02 (1040, 0x410). A (hypothetic) ECU provided message we can read the current engine torque from

ddObj.Name: checksum
ddObj.ddProperty: Instance of signals.checksum. Message related checksum. The sum is defined such that the arithmetic sum of all message bytes (including the check sum itself) and the start value yields 0xff

ddObj.Name: sequenceCounter
ddObj.ddProperty: Instance of signals.sequenceCounter. Sequence counter of message origin. Each update of the message contents results in a cylically decreased counter value. The counter wraps around from 1 to 15

ddObj.Name: torque
ddObj.ddProperty: Instance of signals.torque. Current engine torque as estimated by the ECU

ddObj.Name: LocalScaling
ddObj.ddProperty: Local linear scaling for signal torque

ddObj.Name: pck_API_PT_UserLimits_2032
ddObj.ddProperty: Global (external) struct, which forms the data based API to access the signal values of frame UserLimits (2032, 0x7f0). User command: New limits have been set for supervision of speed of rotation and power. This is a purely data change driven frame, it is not sent until the user changes a least one of the limits

ddObj.Name: sequenceCounter
ddObj.ddProperty: Instance of signals.sequenceCounter. Sequence counter of message origin. Each update of the message contents results in a cylically increased counter value. The counter wraps around from 14 to 1

ddObj.Name: minSpeedOfRotation
ddObj.ddProperty: Instance of signals.minSpeedOfRotation. User set minimum for speeed of rotation. A CAN frame with according status bit is broadcasted by the supervising instance if the speed falls below this limit

ddObj.Name: LocalScaling
ddObj.ddProperty: Local linear scaling for signal minSpeedOfRotation

ddObj.Name: maxSpeedOfRotation
ddObj.ddProperty: Instance of signals.maxSpeedOfRotation. User set maximum for speeed of rotation. A CAN frame with according status bit is broadcasted by the supervising instance if the limit is exceeded

ddObj.Name: LocalScaling
ddObj.ddProperty: Local linear scaling for signal maxSpeedOfRotation

ddObj.Name: checksum
ddObj.ddProperty: Instance of signals.checksum. Message related checksum. The sum is defined such that the arithmetic sum of all message bytes (including the check sum itself) and the start value yields 0xff

ddObj.Name: minPower
ddObj.ddProperty: Instance of signals.minPower. User set minimum for the engine power. A CAN frame with according status bit is broadcasted by the supervising instance if the power falls below this limit

ddObj.Name: LocalScaling
ddObj.ddProperty: Local linear scaling for signal minPower

ddObj.Name: maxPower
ddObj.ddProperty: Instance of signals.maxPower. User set maximum for the engine power. A CAN frame with according status bit is broadcasted by the supervising instance if the limit is exceeded

ddObj.Name: LocalScaling
ddObj.ddProperty: Local linear scaling for signal maxPower

ddObj.Name: pck_API_PT_InfoPowerDisplay_1536
ddObj.ddProperty: Global (external) struct, which forms the data based API to access the signal values of frame InfoPowerDisplay (1536, 0x600). A new CAN message which is sent by the control unit, which is implemented by the demonstration code. It broadcasts the current engine power to other network nodes

ddObj.Name: checksum
ddObj.ddProperty: Instance of signals.checksum. Message related checksum. The sum is defined such that the arithmetic sum of all message bytes (including the check sum itself) and the start value yields 0xff

ddObj.Name: sequenceCounter
ddObj.ddProperty: Instance of signals.sequenceCounter. Sequence counter of message origin. Each update of the message contents results in a cylically increased counter value. The counter wraps around after 14

ddObj.Name: power
ddObj.ddProperty: Instance of signals.power. The computed, current output power of the engine

ddObj.Name: LocalScaling
ddObj.ddProperty: Local linear scaling for signal power

ddObj.Name: state
ddObj.ddProperty: Instance of signals.state. The status of the power computation. If the input information is invalid or suspicious or if there is an overflow in the computation then the computed power is unreliable. This status information will indicate whether the power information is reliabale or not and why not

ddObj.Name: pck_API_PT_StatusPowerDisplay_1537
ddObj.ddProperty: Global (external) struct, which forms the data based API to access the signal values of frame StatusPowerDisplay (1537, 0x601). Status of power display operation. Error events are counted and broadcasted.whenever the status changes. If no change occurs then the status frame is repeated.every 1000 ms

ddObj.Name: noDlcErrors
ddObj.ddProperty: Instance of signals.noDlcErrors. Number of recognized DLC errors in CAN input

ddObj.Name: noCheckSumErrors
ddObj.ddProperty: Instance of signals.noCheckSumErrors. Number of recognized checksum errors in CAN input

ddObj.Name: noSqcErrors
ddObj.ddProperty: Instance of signals.noSqcErrors. Number of recognized sequence errors in CAN input

ddObj.Name: sequenceCounter
ddObj.ddProperty: Instance of signals.sequenceCounter. Sequence counter of message. The counter is incremented prior to sending the frame. The counter wraps around from 126 to 1. 0 and 127 are invalid values

ddObj.Name: checksum
ddObj.ddProperty: Instance of signals.checksum. Message related checksum. The sum is defined such that the arithmetic sum of all message bytes (including the check sum itself) and the start value yields 0xff

ddObj.Name: pck_API_PT_LimitsPowerDisplay_1538
ddObj.ddProperty: Global (external) struct, which forms the data based API to access the signal values of frame LimitsPowerDisplay (1538, 0x602). If a user set limit for speed of rotation or power is crossed (in either direction) then a related status bit is updated and sending this frame is triggered. This is a purely data change driven frame, it is not sent if no data change appears

ddObj.Name: sequenceCounter
ddObj.ddProperty: Instance of signals.sequenceCounter. Sequence counter of message origin. Each update of the message contents results in a cylically decreased counter value. The counter wraps around from 1 to 6

ddObj.Name: belowMinSpeedOfRotation
ddObj.ddProperty: Instance of signals.belowMinSpeedOfRotation. Boolean: True if and only if the speed of rotation is currently below the user set minimum

ddObj.Name: aboveMaxSpeedOfRotation
ddObj.ddProperty: Instance of signals.aboveMaxSpeedOfRotation. Boolean: True if and only if the speed of rotation is currently above the user set maximum

ddObj.Name: belowMinPower
ddObj.ddProperty: Instance of signals.belowMinPower. Boolean: True if and only if the engine power is currently below the user set minimum

ddObj.Name: aboveMaxPower
ddObj.ddProperty: Instance of signals.aboveMaxPower. Boolean: True if and only if the engine power is currently above the user set maximum
